describe
 - groups specs into the same category

it
 - contains the description of the spec
 - contains the verification that the spec was implemented

hspec
 - displays the spec categories as a headers
 - displays one row for each spec
 - displays a '-' for successfully implemented specs
 - displays a 'x' for unsuccessfully implmented specs
 - displays a '-' for pending specs
 - displays a '#' and an additional message for pending specs
 - can output to stdout
 - can output to stdout in color
     # near future, perhaps using System.Console.ANSI?
 - can output to an ascii text file
     # near future
 - can output as xml
     # not so near future
 - can output as html
     # not so near future
 - summarizes the time it takes to finish
 - summarizes the number of examples and failures

quantify (internal)
 - returns an amount and a description given an amount and description
 - returns a singular description given the number 1
 - returns a plural description given a number greater than 1
 - returns a plural description given the number 0
 - handles describing the plural of words that end with an 'x'
     # no need for this yet

Finished in 0.0 seconds

21 examples, 0 failures
